The Heyman Center for the Humanities
Schedule of Events, Spring 2006

For more information about any or all of these events,
please visit http://www.heymancenter.org.

Please note: Patti Smith tickets are $5, and
available at Miller Theater Box Office.
On-line registration is required for "Reporting War"--
see below for instructions.
ALL OTHER EVENTS ARE FREE AND OPEN TO THE PUBLIC.
SEATING IS FIRST COME FIRST SERVED and
NO RESERVATIONS ARE REQUIRED.

PATTI SMITH
"An Evening of Poetry and Acoustic Song with Patti Smith"
Tuesday, February 7, 8pm, Miller Theater
Tickets, $5, available at the Miller Theater Box Office,
Broadway at 116th, or call (212) 854-7799.

CHRISTOPHER RICKS=20
Public Lecture: "True Friendship: Geoffrey Hill and T.S. Eliot"=20
Wednesday, February 15, 6pm, Common Room, Heyman Center=20

CHRISTOPHER RICKS
Seminar: "Editing: Some Cases, Mental and Other"
Thursday, February 16, 10am, Common Room, Heyman Center=20

"A SINGULAR MODERNITY?" =20
A conference co-sponsored by the=20
Southern Asian Institute. =20
Speakers: Arjun Appadurai, Partha Chatterjee,
Sudipta Kaviraj, Steven Lukes, Sheldon Pollock,
Sanjay Subrahmanyam, and David Washbrook
Saturday, February 18, 9:30am-6pm
Dag Hammarskjold Room, 15th Floor, International Affairs Bldg.

GORDON WOOD [Lionel Trilling Seminar]=20
"Does History Teach Any Lessons?"
Respondents: Harry Harootunian, NYU
Robert Ferguson, Columbia University
Thursday, February 23, 6pm, Low Rotunda

ELAINE SCARRY, JOHN HOLLANDER, SHIRLEY HAZZARD,
ALEXANDER NEHAMAS, and MARIE PONSOT
"Beauty and Morals: Some Literary Perspectives"
A symposium, in collaboration with Poets' House
Wednesday, March 22, 6pm,
Davis Auditorium, Schapiro Center

STANLEY CAVELL AND JOHN MCDOWELL, a symposium, Title TBA
Thursday, March 23, 6:15pm,
President's Room, Faculty House

FRANK KERMODE [2006 Edward Said Memorial Lecture]
"Living on a Hyphen: the Anglo-Irish Yeats"
Thursday, March 30, 6pm, President's Room, Faculty House

ORLANDO PATTERSON [Lionel Trilling Seminar]
"The Perils of Freedom in America"
Respondent: Eric Foner
Thursday, April 13, 6pm Rotunda, Low Library

ROBERT FISK, CHARLES GLASS, JOHN PILGER, SEYMOUR HERSH
"Reporting War"
Friday, April 14, 2-5pm, Faculty Room, Low Library
Please Note: REGISTRATION IS REQUIRED FOR THIS EVENT:
Please e-mail your full name to register@heymancenter.org.

"MORAL AND PSYCHOLOGICAL WEAKNESS"
A Two-Day Conference
Speakers: George Ainslie, Michael Bratman, David Bromwich,
Jon Elster, A.D. Nuttall, and Gary Watson
April 21-22, Common Room, Heyman Center, East Campus
Friday: 9:30am-6pm
Saturday: 9:30am-1:30pm

A POSTHUMOUS BOOK-LAUNCH FOR EDWARD SAID,
*On Late Style: Music and Literature Against the Grain*
Co-sponsored by Knopf=20
Monday, April 24, 6:15pm, President's Room, Faculty House=20

STEVEN PINKER,
"The Blank Slate: The Modern Denial of Human Nature"
Thursday, April 27, 7pm,
Proskauer Auditorium, Rm 104, Jerome Greene Hall=20

For more information, please visit www.heymancenter.org


For maps showing the locations of our events,=20
please see the following websites.

Heyman Center
http://www.columbia.edu/about_columbia/map/heyman.html

Miller Theater
http://www.columbia.edu/about_columbia/map/miller_theater.html

Faculty House
http://www.columbia.edu/about_columbia/map/faculty_house.html

Low Library
http://www.columbia.edu/about_columbia/map/low.html

International Affairs Building
http://www.columbia.edu/about_columbia/map/international_affairs.html

Jerome Greene Hall (Law School)
http://www.columbia.edu/about_columbia/map/greene.html

